http://www.thehindu.com/business/Stocks-post-20-month-closing-low-as-crude-muddles-outlook/article14012036.ece

The Sensex closed at its lowest level in 20 months on Thursday due to risk aversion as crude oil resumed its slide and put pressure on Asian markets.The benchmark BSE index ended 0.41 percent lower at 23,962.21, its lowest close since May 15, 2014.The broader NSE index ended 0.44 percent lower at 7,276.80, its lowest close since May 30, 2014.